on-negative Ricci curvature, Journal of Mathematical Analysis and Applications, Vol.415, Issue 1, 25-32,2014.</p>\n<p>41. Yong Lin, Ricci curvature and functional inequalities on graphs, Fifth International Congress of Chinese Mathematicians. Part 1, 2, 663–675, AMS/IP Stud. Adv. Math., 51, pt. 1, 2, Amer. Math. Soc., Providence, RI, 2012.</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-indent: 14px;\">42．</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"text-indent: 14px; line-height: 125%;\">Yong Lin, Gapor Lippner, Shing-Tung Yau, Quantum tunneling on graphs, Communications in Mathematical Physics, Vol.311, no. 1, 113-132, 2012.</span></p>\n<p>43. Yong Lin, Linyuan Lu and Shing-Tung Yau, Ricci curvature of graphs, &nbsp;Tohoku Mathematical Journal, Vol.63, no.4, 605-627, 2011.</p>\n<p>44. Yong Lin and Shing-Tung Yau, Ricci curvature and eigenvalue estimate on locally finite graphs, Mathematical Research Letter, Vol.17, No.2, 345-358, 2010.</p>\n<p>45. Yong Lin, Gapor Lippner, Dan Mangaubi, Shing-Tung Yau, Nodal Geometry of graphs on Surfaces, Discrete and Continuous Dynamical System, Vol.28, No.3, 1291-1298, 2010.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:8px;line-height:125%\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"line-height:125%\">46. Yong Lin, Lifeng Xi, Lipschitz Continuity of Harmonic Function on Graphs, Journal of Mathematical Analysis and Applications, Vol.366, Issue 2, 673-679,2010.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:8px;line-height:125%\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"text-indent: 14px;\">47. Yong Lin, Huojun Ruan, Maximal functions and Fourier transforms of self-similar measures, Chaos,Solitons and Fractals,Vol. 27</span><span style=\"text-indent: 14px;\">，</span><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"text-indent: 14px;\">2006.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:8px;line-height:125%\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"text-indent: 14px;\">48. Dachun Yang, Yong Lin, Spaces of Lipschitz type on metric spaces and their applications, Proc. Edinb. Math. Soc(2) 47, No.3, 709-752, 2004.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-top:8px;line-heigh